<TITLE> Shamsuzzaman Khan new Bangla Academy DG </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 24 (bdnews24.com)The government has appointed Shamsuzzaman Khan to Bangla Academy as director general, an establishment ministry order said on Sunday. The order said the two-year contractual appointment will come into effect from the date of his joining. The ministry also announced a few more contractual appointments and transfers. Dhaka Range police's additional DIG, current charge, Mojammel Hossain, has been moved to the establishment ministry as officer on special duty. (OSD) the health ministry's retired joint secretary Makhduma Nargis has been appointed director to the ministry's Community Clinic Project for two years with the rank of additional secretary. Retired army officer major Golam Kibria Khan Chowdhury will head Bangladesh Haor and Swamps Development Board director general for three years. Deputy secretary Abu Sadeque, director at the Bureau of Disaster Management, has been transferred to the food ministry. The Board of Investment's oversees appointment branch director, deputy secretary Mamdud Hossain Alamgir, has been made OSD at the establishment ministry. bd
